BT 0 g /F2 18 Tf 167.76 740 Td (Topic 1: Recognizing Scam Emails) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 80 720 m 532 720 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 690 Td (- Look for misspellings and poor grammar in the email.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 660 Td (- Check the sender's email address carefully - scammers use fake addresses.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 630 Td (- Be suspicious of urgent language like 'Act now!' or 'Your account is locked!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 600 Td (- Never click links in emails from unknown senders.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 570 Td (- Hover over links to see where they really go before clicking.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 540 Td (- Legitimate companies will never ask for your password by email.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 510 Td (- If an email offers money or prizes you did not enter to win, it is a scam.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 480 Td (- When in doubt, call the company directly using the number on their website.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 450 Td (- Forward suspicious emails to the company's fraud department.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 420 Td (- Delete scam emails - do not reply or unsubscribe \(this confirms your address\).) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
