BT 0 g /F2 18 Tf 159.12 740 Td (Topic 2: Creating Strong Passwords) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 80 720 m 532 720 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 690 Td (- Use at least 12 characters - longer is always stronger.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 660 Td (- Mix uppercase letters, lowercase letters, numbers, and symbols.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 630 Td (- Never use personal information like birthdays, pet names, or addresses.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 600 Td (- Avoid common words like 'password', '123456', or 'qwerty'.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 570 Td (- Use a different password for each important account.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 540 Td (- Consider using a passphrase: 'My-Dog-Loves-Walks-At-7pm!' is very strong.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 510 Td (- Write passwords in a secure physical notebook kept in a safe place.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 480 Td (- Consider a password manager app to remember all your passwords.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 450 Td (- Change passwords immediately if you suspect any account was compromised.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 420 Td (- Never share passwords with anyone, even family members for shared accounts.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
