BT 0 g /F2 18 Tf 115.92000000000002 740 Td (Topic 6: Two-Factor Authentication Explained) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 80 720 m 532 720 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 690 Td (- Two-factor authentication \(2FA\) adds a second layer of security to your accounts.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 660 Td (- Even if someone steals your password, they cannot get in without the second factor.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 630 Td (- The most common second factor is a code sent to your phone by text message.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 600 Td (- When you log in, you enter your password then the code from your phone.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 570 Td (- Enable 2FA on your email, bank, and social media accounts first.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 540 Td (- Some services use an app like Google Authenticator instead of text messages.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 510 Td (- Keep a backup phone number or recovery codes in case you lose your phone.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 480 Td (- 2FA takes an extra 10 seconds but makes your account much more secure.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 450 Td (- Most banks and email providers offer 2FA in their security settings.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 420 Td (- Think of 2FA like a double lock on your front door - extra protection.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
