BT 0 g /F2 18 Tf 167.76 740 Td (Topic 9: Recognizing Phone Scams) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 80 720 m 532 720 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 690 Td (- If a caller says you owe money and must pay immediately, it is a scam.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 660 Td (- The IRS and government agencies communicate by mail, not threatening phone calls.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 630 Td (- Never give credit card or bank information to someone who calls you.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 600 Td (- Scammers can fake caller ID to show a real company's phone number.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 570 Td (- If someone claims to be from your bank, hang up and call the number on your card.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 540 Td (- Be suspicious of calls saying a grandchild is in trouble and needs money.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 510 Td (- Never pay anything with gift cards - this is always a scam method.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 480 Td (- Register your number on the Do Not Call list at donotcall.gov.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 450 Td (- Let unknown numbers go to voicemail - legitimate callers leave messages.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 420 Td (- Report scam calls to the FTC at reportfraud.ftc.gov.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
