BT 0 g /F2 18 Tf 141.84 740 Td (Topic 17: What to Do If You Are Hacked) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 80 720 m 532 720 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 690 Td (- Change your passwords immediately, starting with email and banking.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 660 Td (- Enable two-factor authentication on all important accounts.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 630 Td (- Check your bank accounts for unauthorized transactions.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 600 Td (- Contact your bank immediately if you see charges you did not make.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 570 Td (- Run a full antivirus scan on your computer and phone.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 540 Td (- Check if your email is sending messages you did not write.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 510 Td (- Notify your contacts that your account was compromised.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 480 Td (- Place a fraud alert on your credit reports through the three bureaus.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 450 Td (- File a report with the FTC at identitytheft.gov if your identity was stolen.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 12 Tf 70 420 Td (- Consider getting professional help from your device manufacturer or a tech expert.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
